<subSubSection id="58E26547FFBCFFFEFF642B0EFCAAF828" pageId="10" pageNumber="311" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="104736CCFFBCFFFEFF642B0EFCAAF828" blockId="10.[151,1436,1725,2038]" pageId="10" pageNumber="311">
<emphasis id="228CEADEFFBCFFFEFF642B0EFED4F89F" bold="true" box="[199,315,1833,1858]" pageId="10" pageNumber="311">Remarks.</emphasis>
The specimen from 
<collectingCountry id="68EF765CFFBCFFFEFD922B0EFD6CF89F" box="[561,643,1833,1858]" name="Taiwan" pageId="10" pageNumber="311">Taiwan</collectingCountry>
differs from the 
<typeStatus id="CF43886EFFBCFFFEFCEC2B0DFC90F89F" box="[847,895,1834,1858]" pageId="10" pageNumber="311">type</typeStatus>
material of 
<taxonomicName id="D7F84D4FFFBCFFFEFBB12B0DFB50F89F" authorityName="Saito" authorityYear="2011" box="[1042,1215,1833,1858]" class="Polyplacophora" family="Leptochitonidae" genus="Leptochiton" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neoloricata" pageId="10" pageNumber="311" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="bergenhayni">
<emphasis id="228CEADEFFBCFFFEFBB12B0DFB50F89F" box="[1042,1215,1833,1858]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="311">L. bergenhayni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by having a white tegmentum (vs. beige with irregular white maculation in 
<typeStatus id="CF43886EFFBCFFFEFC822B69FCB3F8BB" box="[801,860,1870,1894]" pageId="10" pageNumber="311">types</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName id="D7F84D4FFFBCFFFEFC272B69FBC0F8BB" authorityName="Saito" authorityYear="2011" box="[900,1071,1869,1894]" class="Polyplacophora" family="Leptochitonidae" genus="Leptochiton" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neoloricata" pageId="10" pageNumber="311" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="bergenhayni">
<emphasis id="228CEADEFFBCFFFEFC272B69FBC0F8BB" box="[900,1071,1869,1894]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="311">L. bergenhayni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), long smooth marginal needles (vs. only grooved marginal needles in 
<typeStatus id="CF43886EFFBCFFFEFDEF2B55FD68F857" box="[588,647,1906,1930]" pageId="10" pageNumber="311">types</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName id="D7F84D4FFFBCFFFEFD0C2B55FCB6F857" authorityName="Saito" authorityYear="2011" box="[687,857,1905,1930]" class="Polyplacophora" family="Leptochitonidae" genus="Leptochiton" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neoloricata" pageId="10" pageNumber="311" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="bergenhayni">
<emphasis id="228CEADEFFBCFFFEFD0C2B55FD51F854" box="[687,702,1906,1929]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="311">L</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="228CEADEFFBCFFFEFD6D2B56FCB6F857" box="[718,857,1905,1930]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="311">bergenhayni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), ventral scales near margin with 2–4 ribs in distal part (vs. keeled at distal half in 
<typeStatus id="CF43886EFFBCFFFEFDA72BB1FDD0F873" box="[516,575,1942,1966]" pageId="10" pageNumber="311">types</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName id="D7F84D4FFFBCFFFEFDC42BB1FCFDF873" authorityName="Saito" authorityYear="2011" box="[615,786,1941,1966]" class="Polyplacophora" family="Leptochitonidae" genus="Leptochiton" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neoloricata" pageId="10" pageNumber="311" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="bergenhayni">
<emphasis id="228CEADEFFBCFFFEFDC42BB1FCFDF873" box="[615,786,1941,1966]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="311">L. bergenhayni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
). Taking into account the difference in habitat depth and distance between the 
<typeStatus id="CF43886EFFBCFFFEFE2F2B9DFE53F80F" box="[396,444,1978,2002]" pageId="10" pageNumber="311">type</typeStatus>
locality (
<collectingCountry id="68EF765CFFBCFFFEFD8A2B9DFD83F80F" box="[553,620,1978,2002]" name="Japan" pageId="10" pageNumber="311">Japan</collectingCountry>
) and the 
<collectingCountry id="68EF765CFFBCFFFEFD7B2B9EFCC5F80F" box="[728,810,1977,2002]" name="Taiwan" pageId="10" pageNumber="311">Taiwan</collectingCountry>
population, I consider these morphological differences within the range of intraspecific variation for 
<taxonomicName id="D7F84D4FFFBCFFFEFD362BF9FCD1F82B" authorityName="Saito" authorityYear="2011" box="[661,830,2013,2038]" class="Polyplacophora" family="Leptochitonidae" genus="Leptochiton" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neoloricata" pageId="10" pageNumber="311" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="bergenhayni">
<emphasis id="228CEADEFFBCFFFEFD362BF9FCD1F82B" box="[661,830,2013,2038]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="311">L. bergenhayni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
